Citation.sTitle: Temperature Dependence of Vapor Pressures over Saturated Aqueous Solutions at Invariant Points of the NaCl + KCl + H2O, NaCl + NaNO3 + H2O, KCl + KBr + H2O, KCl + KI + H2O, KCl + KNO3 + H2O, and KCl + K2SO4 + H2O Systems
Citation.sAbstract: Vapor pressures of water over saturated solutions with regard to two salts, in the NaCl + KCl + H2O, NaCl + NaNO3 + H2O, KCl + KBr + H2O, KCl + KI + H2O, KCl + KNO3 + H2O, and KCl + K2SO4 + H2O systems, are reported in the (278 to 323) K temperature range. The determined vapor pressures served to obtain the water activities, the osmotic coefficients, and the molar enthalpies of vaporization.
